es of governance and control that must remain available to interpretation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aDigital mediaxPhilosophy. 0aElectronic publications. 0aElectronic publishing. 0aLiterature and technology. 4acode. 4adigital. 4ahardware. 4ahistory. 4ahumanism. 4aliterary theory. 4amedia. 4asoftware. 4atechnology. 4atext. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360234240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503602342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503602342.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles